      "gridPos": { "h": 11, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 27 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Architecture at a glance\n\n- **5 microservices in Go** — Spider, Conductor, Cartographer, Searcher, Frontend — talking over gRPC, including a bidirectional streaming pipeline for crawl ingestion\n- **PageRank from scratch** — damping factor 0.85, 100 random-sample sweeps of up to 100K pages each, recomputed every 6 hours by a Kubernetes CronJob\n- **Ranking formula** — relevance blends PostgreSQL full-text score (30%) with PageRank (70%), served off a GIN-indexed `search_vector` column\n- **Self-hosted infrastructure** — Kubernetes (k3s) on Hetzner Cloud, provisioned with OpenTofu/Terraform, images built and pushed to a private container registry\n- **Real observability** — this dashboard runs on the same Prometheus + Grafana + Alertmanager stack that pages the on-call engineer (me) on Slack\n- **Defense in depth** — SSRF protection against private/metadata IP ranges, per-domain rate limiting, robots.txt compliance, gRPC circuit breakers, and NetworkPolicy-enforced zero-trust segmentation between every service"
      }
    },
